B. Redundant catalogs
Store catalog copies in:

Local disk

NAS

Cloud cold storage

C. File signature verification
Detect file type mismatches (e.g., JPEG renamed to PNG).

D. EXIF integrity checking
For photo archives:

Hash EXIF separately

Detect metadata corruption early

E. Repository aging analytics
Track:

Rate of corruption

File types most affected

Drives most prone to bit rot

F. Auto‑repair hooks
If you store redundant copies, the software could:

Automatically restore corrupted files

Flag files for manual review

